<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She decamped from her Los Angeles home to a scenic spot in Upstate New York.</p>

<p>And Gwyneth Paltrow couldn't help but show off her extraordinary view on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The 48-year-old Royal Tenenbaums star shared a photo to her Instagram Stories revealing her breathtaking breakfast table on the edge of Upper Saranac Lake.</p>

<p>Stunning: Gwyneth Paltrow, 48, revealed her gorgeous view from the luxury resort The Point in Upstate New York in her Instagram Stories on Wednesday</p>

<p>Gwyneth tagged the photo, revealing she was staying at the luxurious hotel The Point, which sits on 75 acres by the lake.</p>

<p>Her husband Brad Falchuk was seated at the table with his breakfast in the photo, which was on a deck above the water.</p>

<p>Ahead of them was the lake and the untouched forest, and the sky was meditative and overcast.</p>

<p>The Point is one of the resorts recommended on the actress' Goop lifestyle site, so it was a logical choice for the couple to stay after celebrating her 48th birthday.</p>

<p>Going strong: The day before, the two posed for their two-year anniversary photo against the Upper Saranac Lake. Their resort costs a minimum of $1,750 per night, and two-night stays are often required</p>

<p>Tradition: 'Year two, through,' she captioned the photo, which was reminiscent of an anniversary snap from a year earlier in which she wrote, 'Year one, done'</p>

<p>Its website states that reservations are all inclusive, and guests can expect to pay a minimum of $1,750 per night, and most reservations require guests to stay a minimum of two nights.</p>

<p>The resort also boasts about its lack of TVs and spotty cell reception, allowing guests to disconnect.</p>

<p>On Tuesday, Gwyneth shared a lovely photo of her clear makeup-free face as she posed with Brad by the lake.</p>

<p>She covered up against the breeze in a down vest, while he wore a thick olive cardigan. </p>

<p>The Se7en star was celebrating her two year anniversary with her TV producer husband, whom she married in September 2018 in the Hamptons. </p>

<p>'Year two, through,' she captioned the photo, which was reminiscent of an anniversary snap from a year earlier in which she wrote, 'Year one, done.'</p>

<p>Smitten: On Sunday, the American Horror Story co-creator shared a playful photo of Gwyneth in a red dress as she lounged on a black leather sofa as he called her a 'bada**'</p>

<p>On Sunday, the American Horror Story co-creator shared a playful photo of Gwyneth in a red dress as she lounged on a black leather sofa while wearing Ugg boots.</p>

<p>He called her a 'bada**' and complimented her cooking and cocktail skills, while adding that, 'She makes friends feel like family and family feel like friends.</p>

<p>'Trust me, she's the best.'</p>

<p>For her own birthday fun, Gwyneth posted outdoors with nothing on at all while showcasing her admirable physique.</p>

<p>'In nothing but my birthday suit today... thank you all so much for the birthday wishes,' she wrote before plugging a Goop product. </p>

